        arteries could not be correct.
        <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Harvey</ENAMEX> also observed that the heart was a contractile muscle with one-way valves between
        the <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">chambers</ENAMEX> on each side. He measured the volume of the left ventricle of dead human
