        heart. He measured that the heart beat <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">60–100</NUMEX> times per minute. Therefore, the volume of
        blood expelled from the left <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ventricle per hour</NUMEX> was <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">about 60 ml × 1/8</NUMEX> × <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">60</NUMEX> beats/minute ×
        <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">60 minutes/hour</TIMEX>, or <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">27</NUMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">liters</ENAMEX>/hour. However, the average human has <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">only 5.5</NUMEX> liters of blood
